title: Pitfalls to avoid when working with agencies
text:
Coming from personal experience, there are tons of ways working with an agency can go wrong. I’ve spent $120k working with 4 agencies: SEO, paid acquisition, conversion copywriting, and design.

I also know the situation from the other side, as I run a development marketplace to hire vetted engineers (http://lemon.io).

Having matched hundreds of developers with startups and worked with agencies myself, I found what makes choosing an agency a success. Sharing my personal checklist:

Ask HN: Who Games on Mac OS?
text:
I bought a 2019 16' MacBook Pro i7 with a Radeon 5300 graphics card to run Windows and game. I've been impressed so far - running the Witcher 3 next-gen update without a hitch. Yeah, sure, it's loud as hell, but I've ordered a fan from Svalt which will hopefully keep that down and improve performance even more.

Does anyone recommend any games in particular? Any games that don't work well? Looking to try Elden Ring soon.

I also have an M1 Pro that my work gave me with 32GB of RAM, and I've run Parallels on it and am able to run old games at 120fps (playing Vampire the Masquerade from 08, for example) but the first Witcher game from 08 is terribly buggy and glitchy.

Leave you favorite games and Steam IDs if you want.
